org.team5940.robot_core.modules.camera_streaming

Class SelectableMJPEGStreamerModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.team5940.robot_core.modules.AbstractModule
      • org.team5940.robot_core.modules.ownable.AbstractOwnableModule
        • org.team5940.robot_core.modules.control.procedures.AbstractProcedureModule
          • org.team5940.robot_core.modules.camera_streaming.SelectableMJPEGStreamerModule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable, ProcedureModule, Module, OwnableModule

    public class SelectableMJPEGStreamerModule
extends AbstractProcedureModule
    An implementation of AbstractProcedureModule that streams whatever VideoSource is selected by a SelectorModule. It can also run the images through an array of MatProcessorModules.

      • SelectableMJPEGStreamerModule

        public SelectableMJPEGStreamerModule(java.lang.String name,
                                     LoggerModule logger,
                                     SelectorModule selector,
                                     VideoSource unselectedSource,
                                     VideoSource[] sources,
                                     MatProcessorModule[] processors)
                              throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Initializes a new SelectableMJPEGStreamerModule.
        Parameters:
        name - This' name.
        logger - This' logger.
        selector - Chooses which camera to display.
        unselectedSource - The camera displayed when the selector's state is -1.
        sources - The video sources to switch between.
        processors - The processors run on the image before it is displayed.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if any argument is null, the number of selector states is not equal to the number of sources, if sources contains null, or processors contains null.
